1301":"1301","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","about 1297":"about 1297","1271":"1271","Abt. 1271":"about 1271","Bokesworth, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire,, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bourgoyne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile.","Americanized form of French   Bourgoin  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bourgoin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alphee, Alyre, Andre, Armand, Aurore, Celina, Emile, Gilberte, Jacques, Laurent, Lucienne, Olivier.","French:","variant of <b>Bourgouin</b> (and, in North America, an altered form of this), a habitational name for someone from Burgundy (Old French <i>Bourgogne</i>), a region of eastern France having Dijon as its center. The area was invaded by the <i>Burgundii</i>, an ancient Germanic tribe from whom it takes its name, in about  AD  480. The duchy of Burgundy, created in 877 by Charles II, King of the Western Franks, was extremely powerful in the later Middle Ages, especially under Philip the Bold (1342–1404; duke from 1363). Compare   Bourgoyne   and   Bourguignon  ."]}]},{"name":"Barthelmew","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: from an altered form of the personal name <i>Bartholomaeus</i> (see   Bartholomew  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Barthelmess","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt.","German: variant of   Barthelmes  . Compare   Bartmess  ."]},{"name":"Bartimus","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Barthelmes   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."]},{"name":"Bartholomew","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Barthelmew Bourgoyne was born about 1271, in Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Elizabeth De Vere in 1295, in Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1301, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 31."},"et":{"Abt. 1271–1301":"umbes 1271–1301","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1297–1332":"1297–1332","1271–1301":"1271–1301","1301":"1301","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","about 1297":"umbes 1297","1271":"1271","Abt. 1271":"umbes 1271","Bokesworth, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire,, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt. 1271–1301":"noin 1271–1301","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","1297–1332":"1297–1332","1271–1301":"1271–1301","1301":"1301","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","about 1297":"noin 1297","1271":"1271","Abt. 1271":"noin 1271","Bokesworth, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire,, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt. 1271–1301":"environ 1271–1301","1275–Female":"1275–Décédée","1297–1332":"1297–1332","1271–1301":"1271–1301","1301":"1301","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","about 1297":"environ 1297","1271":"1271","Abt. 1271":"environ 1271","Bokesworth, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire,, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Barthelme